<%= faq_schema([
  { question: "How is swim pace calculated?", answer: "Swim pace is calculated by dividing total time by distance, then normalizing to per-100 units. For example, if you swim 400 meters in 8 minutes (480 seconds), your pace is (480/400) x 100 = 120 seconds per 100m, or 2:00/100m. The calculator also converts between meters and yards automatically." },
  { question: "What is a good swim pace per 100m?", answer: "For recreational swimmers, 2:00-2:30 per 100m is common. Intermediate swimmers typically swim 1:40-2:00/100m. Advanced competitive swimmers may be under 1:20/100m, and elite swimmers can hold 1:00-1:10/100m for middle distances. Pace varies significantly with stroke, distance, and pool versus open water." },
  { question: "How do you convert between meters and yards?", answer: "One meter equals 1.09361 yards. To convert a per-100m pace to per-100y, divide by 1.09361. For example, a 2:00/100m pace equals approximately 1:50/100y. Swimming in a yard pool produces slightly faster times for the same distance because 100 yards is shorter than 100 meters." },
  { question: "Why do estimated times slow down for longer distances?", answer: "The calculator applies fatigue factors to longer distance estimates. When swimming longer, pace naturally slows due to energy system limitations, lactate accumulation, and muscular fatigue. A swimmer's 100m pace is typically 5-8% faster than their 400m pace, and their 400m pace is roughly 3-6% faster than their 1500m pace." },
  { question: "What is CSS (Critical Swim Speed)?", answer: "CSS (Critical Swim Speed) is the swimming equivalent of lactate threshold pace. It represents the fastest pace a swimmer can sustain aerobically. CSS is commonly calculated from the difference between 400m and 200m time trials. Training at or near CSS improves aerobic endurance and is a key intensity for distance swimmers." }
]) %>

<%= calculator_schema_with_ratings(
  name: "Swim Pace Calculator",
  description: "Calculate swim pace per 100m/100yd and estimate times for various distances.",
  url: health_swim_pace_url,
  category: "HealthApplication",
  calculator_slug: "swim-pace"
) %>

